        "title": "feat(durable): add ops storage and human signal readiness",
        "body": "## Stack / Dependency Note\n\nThis is Batch E in the OpenClaw-X durable-core stack.\n\nDepends on:\n- PR1 / #97507: durable coordination RFC\n- PR2 / #97508: opt-in durable coordination kernel\n- Batch A / #97666: restart and schema lifecycle proof\n- Batch B / #97667: intake, branch routes, Task Flow projection\n- Batch C / #97668: Workboard durable projection visibility\n- Batch D / #97865: worker execution and recovery hardening\n\nGitHub currently shows batch PRs against `main`, so this PR may include earlier dependency commits in the commit list. The intended unique review diff is the ops, storage, and human-signal readiness layer after Batch D.\n\nInternal plan coverage: PR7 + PR8 + PR13.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Adds paginated durable timeline reads and terminal-run compaction support.\n- Adds a durable store factory seam so SQLite remains default while future backends can share conformance behavior.\n- Adds typed human signal gates for durable human-in-the-loop states.\n\n## Why\n\nThis batch makes durable history safer to keep locally, prepares backend selection without forcing Postgres, and gives human waits a durable primitive instead of hiding them in session memory.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- No Postgres backend in this batch.\n- No `chat.send.contextRefs` protocol change.\n- No visual approval UI.\n- No external workflow engine adapter.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `npm test -- src/durable/worker.test.ts src/durable/recovery.test.ts src/durable/executor.test.ts src/durable/routes.test.ts src/durable/sqlite-store.test.ts src/durable/store-factory.test.ts src/durable/human-signal.test.ts src/durable/taskflow-bridge.test.ts src/durable/intake.test.ts src/durable/fan-in.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.browser.test.ts`\n- `npm run ui:build`",
        "branch": "codex/openclaw-durable-batch-e-ops-hitl",
